        "filename": "util/linux/auxiliary_vector.cc",
        "patchSetId": 4
      },
      "lineNbr": 49,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-06-07T21:04:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Check that something’s not already stored at values_[type]? (Unless it’s AT_IGNORE. Maybe you should just skip AT_IGNORE.)\n\nYou can use util/stdlib/map_insert.h MapInsertOrReplace(), using it for its return value and counting on “replace” being harmless if you’re going to return false. Or you can add a MapInsert() there (without the OrReplace() part), use it here, and base MapInsertOrReplace() on the new function.",
      "revId": "13b6807805d3e383205da7e5bba2df355825a2d5",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
