      "writtenOn": "2017-06-07T21:04:34Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This is cool. I’d have tested a few more things here—basically anything in \u003clinux/auxvec.h\u003e that it’s easy to get corroboration of.\n\nNote that I don’t think that this means you should poke getauxval() blindly (although you can certainly do that _in addition_).\n\nYou can, however, do getuid(), geteuid(), getegid(), etc. Since we have /proc/pid/maps reading working, maybe make sure that AT_PHDR goes somewhere valid, same for AT_SYSINFO_EHDR (only on architectures that define it, obviously). Maybe even check AT_BASE_PLATFORM against a few hard-codes based on the CPU, since we’ve got ProcessMemory::ReadCString().",
      "revId": "13b6807805d3e383205da7e5bba2df355825a2d5",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
